name: lung papillary adenocarcinoma
definition: A papillary adenocarcinoma that is located_in the lung. [url:https\://radiopaedia.org/articles/mediastinal-teratoma, url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26766978]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, a lung papillary adenocarcinoma cell line harboring EGFR wild-type and expressing PAK1 demonstrated resistance to Iressa (gefitinib) in culture (PMID: 27178741).

references.title: PAK1 Is a Novel Therapeutic Target in Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitor-Resistant Lung Adenocarcinoma Activated by the PI3K/AKT Signaling Regardless of EGFR Mutation.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, treatment with ABBV-399 resulted in complete response in a MET-over expressing papillary lung adenocarcinoma cell line xenograft model (PMID: 27573171).

references.title: ABBV-399, a c-Met Antibody-Drug Conjugate that Targets Both MET-Amplified and c-Met-Overexpressing Tumors, Irrespective of MET Pathway Dependence.
